# Source Control ignore file
# (Root level .gitignore)

# --- IDEs & OS ---
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- .NET Backend ---
**/bin/
**/obj/
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
build_errors.txt
build.log
errors.log

# --- Angular Frontend ---
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/tmp/
.angular/
.editorconfig-cache
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# --- Local Secrets ---
**/*appsettings.Development.json
# **/*appsettings.json (Removed so Vercel/Railway can see the base config)
# Note: In production you might want to use Env variables instead of commiting appsettings.json.
# But for a simple demo with the user, I'll keep the base appsettings.json so it works on Railway easily.
# I'll only ignore Development specific.

# --- Uploads ---
**/wwwroot/uploads/*
!**/wwwroot/uploads/.gitkeep
